{
  "stem": "12447.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "One was a, a bridge-- a steel bridge-- a steel structure.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The other one was a concrete bridge, like an open bridge.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we went through the steel bridge-- we crossed over the steel bridge.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I think that bridge was called Kierbedz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I get confused between these two bridges which one was which.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But the steel bridge, we crossed by foot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And actually, they stood-- you know, the Polish soldiers stood guard.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they wouldn't let anybody on the bridge.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But my father introduced himself, that he was a, a Polish ex-soldier, and he was an invalid.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And he-- they-- somehow, they always gave him the, like, respect in that-- in that matter.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So when he showed them the documents, they would let us through.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We came through the bridge.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we walked all the way to my uncle, which is-- his name is-- name was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I believe was Moishe.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I am not 100% sure.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "It was Avram or Moishe.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I kind of got mixed up at this point.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We stayed during the bombardment-- I would say few weeks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because it continued-- the siege of Warsaw continued, I think, about three weeks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they bombed the city quite often.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I remember we stood in his apartment over there-- in his house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every time they bombed it, we would run down to the cellar, which was a huge cellar.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Which was really stupid to sit in the cellar, because later on we found out that a lot of people sitting in the cellar got buried alive.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But at that point, we thought that this would be the safest place.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the bombardments were quite, quite often.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And at night, we would come out from the cellar and look around.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
